Shall

We can use shall I/shall we to make suggesstions and to offer services to others. 
Shall is often used for very polite suggesstions and offers.
The word will is not used in this way.

Shall I help you with your suitcase?
Not Will I help you with your suitcase?

Shall I bring a dessert to the party?

Shall we go to the theater tonight?

What time shall we make the reservation for?

Let's go and talk to the manager, shall we?

